news.title: SC upholds Bombay HC verdict against rules pushing up land property tax
news.para: The new rules of the BMC had led to much higher property taxes for the developers, who challenged the constitutional validity of the new regime for computing property taxes.

news.title: HSVP & Gurugram development body refuse to check infrastructure at builder floors
news.para: In June this year, the department of town and country planning (DTCP) handed over the responsibility of inspection of all projects, except individual houses and builder floors, to the GMDA.

news.title: What led to Chintels Paradiso cave-in? SIT likely to file report on Nov 8
news.para: Last week, a structural audit report filed by IIT-Delhi had declared the tower of 64 flats not habitable and beyond repair because of construction defects.

news.title: DTCP bans property sale, purchase at a society in Sector 90, Gurugram
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Amit Madholia said that action was taken against the developer as it had entered into an agreement with land owners for providing 35% of saleable area to them but later made pacts with other developers without permission.

news.title: SC recalls order capping 8% interest on land dues in Noida and Greater Noida
news.para: ​A bench of Chief Justice UU Lalit and Ajay Rastogi allowed the application of Noida and Greater Noida seeking recall of the 2020 order on the ground that both the authorities have been suffering huge losses and their functioning have virtually come to a standstill.

news.title: China Evergrande says its Hong Kong land sold by receivers for $637 million
news.para: The land project is expected to result in a loss of about $770 million, the Chinese property developer said in a filing to the Hong Kong bourse. The sale proceeds will be used to repay the financial obligations tied to the land plot, it said.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders Vatika to refund homebuyers money
news.para: The Gurugram bench of the Haryana real estate regulatory authority (HRERA) has ordered Vatika Limited to refund money with interest to all 28 allottees of its housing project which the developer has abandoned.

news.title: Canada: GIC, partner to buy Summit Industrial Income REIT for $3.3 billion
news.para: GIC and Dream Industrial REIT (DIR) will form a joint venture for the deal, with GIC owning 90% and DIR owning the rest, according to the statements.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT's net operating income up 48% at Rs 241.3 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Brookfield India Real Estate Trust informed that the company has declared a distribution of Rs 170.89 crore or Rs 5.10 per unit for the quarter ended September 30, 2022.

news.title: India Cements post Rs 121 crore net loss in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 1,337.70 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of from Rs 1,241.44 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maharashtra government forms committee to streamline realty processes in Navi Mumbai
news.para: CIDCO undertakes various mega infrastructure projects, including the ongoing Navi Mumbai International Airport, Navi Mumbai Metro, NAINA, Corporate Park etc. The town planning body has allotted land parcels on lease to different real estate developers to create residential and commercial projects.

news.title: L&T Realty and CapitaLand India Trust to develop six million sq ft office spaces
news.para: Depending on the completion of these developments, CLINT expects majority of the capital commitment for the projects to start from H2 2024 onwards.

news.title: Over 15,000 objections & suggestions received on Navi Mumbai draft development plan
news.para: Now, the NMMC will soon conduct hearings on the suggestions and objections received and prepare the final draft to be submitted to the state government for further approval.

news.title: Raipur civic body to ease process for transfer of land ownership
news.para: Besides, all types of taxes can also be deposited online without going to the RMC offices. The existing method of name transfer in land cases takes more than two months to complete.

news.title: One year on, Nagpur development body yet to execute PMAY lease deeds
news.para: Stamp duty is charged around 7% of the total value of flat in the city. The total cost of a PMAY flat is Rs9.15 lakh, thus the stamp duty amount comes to Rs64,050.
